13:31.686 --> 13:32.812
Hmm.

13:32.812 --> 13:34.981
And that's--that--
that's interesting.

13:42.113 --> 13:43.114
Why would Tesla be interested
in them?

13:44.074 --> 13:45.450
Even if they checked them out,

13:45.450 --> 13:46.576
that doesn't mean they thought
it was worth anything.

13:46.576 --> 13:47.952
Can you find out
what the deal is?

13:47.952 --> 13:49.621
You think Chase is gonna tell
me anything

13:49.621 --> 13:50.997
after the way you insulted him?

13:50.997 --> 13:52.248
Well, if Tesla's looking
at them,

13:52.248 --> 13:53.667
maybe other companies are too?

13:53.667 --> 13:56.002
[gasps]
I used to date a guy at GM.

13:56.002 --> 13:57.337
I could do some fishing.

13:57.337 --> 13:58.380
Okay, great. Call him.

13:58.380 --> 13:59.756
Does anyone know someone
at Ford?

13:59.756 --> 14:01.800
I actually had an on-again,
off-again thing

14:01.800 --> 14:03.718
- with a guy there.
- Oh. Call them too.

14:03.718 --> 14:05.762
Um, anyone know anyone
at Chrysler?

14:05.762 --> 14:07.138
Throuple that went south.

14:07.138 --> 14:09.557
- Ooh, I'll try him.
- How 'bout Volvo?

14:09.557 --> 14:10.975
Not into Swedes, got it.

14:10.975 --> 14:12.727
I know a VC guy
I could check with.

14:12.727 --> 14:14.396
He usually knows
if something has buzz.

14:14.396 --> 14:15.647
I can call
my hedge-fund friend.

14:15.647 --> 14:16.981
We met in business school,
not a throuple.

14:16.981 --> 14:18.733
- No need to slut-shame.
- I can see if the analyst

14:18.733 --> 14:20.068
who spoke to my class has heard
of 'em.

14:20.068 --> 14:21.695
I could reach out
to the "Journal" reporter.

14:21.695 --> 14:23.113
I'll call them.
I need you to see what else

14:23.113 --> 14:24.447
you can squeeze out
of that engineer.

14:24.447 --> 14:25.532
- He's into you, right?
- You want me

14:25.532 --> 14:27.117
to whore myself out
to the weirdo?

14:27.117 --> 14:28.451
Flirt with him.
I'm not saying you should

14:28.451 --> 14:29.869
[bleep] him.
I mean, unless there was

14:29.869 --> 14:31.037
- a connection and you're into--
- Ew.

14:31.037 --> 14:32.747
Jeff Bezos used
to look like a dork,

14:32.747 --> 14:34.916
and now he's a billionaire
with a Jason Statham vibe.

14:34.916 --> 14:37.252
Okay?
You could do way worse.

14:37.252 --> 14:39.170
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

14:39.170 --> 14:40.922
David, how are you?

14:40.922 --> 14:42.340
Why are you calling, Cyrus?

14:42.340 --> 14:43.758
I've just missed you.

14:43.758 --> 14:46.177
I was thinking about that week
we spent at the beach.

14:46.177 --> 14:47.929
Oh, speaking of beaches,

14:47.929 --> 14:50.015
has GM been talking
to a company called--

14:50.015 --> 14:52.058
Sandbox?
No, that doesn't ring a bell.

14:52.058 --> 14:53.560
It's probably nothing.
I'm just doing

14:53.560 --> 14:55.353
- my due diligence.
- Well, I could ask around

14:55.353 --> 14:56.813
- and call you back.
- Great, thanks.

14:56.813 --> 14:59.774
I'm 99% sure
that they're scam artists, so--

14:59.774 --> 15:01.776
They're gonna be huge.
They got this game-changing

15:01.776 --> 15:04.612
technology, but I need to know
if there's competition.

15:04.612 --> 15:05.655
All right,
thanks for the tip.

15:05.655 --> 15:07.615
No, no.
I'm not giving you a tip.

15:07.615 --> 15:10.035
Hey, Dustin. [laughs]

15:10.035 --> 15:11.536
Dusty Dustin.

15:11.536 --> 15:13.329
[laughs] No, that's not--

15:13.329 --> 15:14.622
