15:26.509 --> 15:27.802
When you spoke
to our class, you said

15:27.802 --> 15:29.137
we can call you with questions?

15:29.137 --> 15:30.555
Can I ask you
about one company?

15:30.555 --> 15:31.973
Sandbox?
Is anyone at the "Journal"

15:31.973 --> 15:33.266
- writing about them?
- Why?

15:33.266 --> 15:34.309
Are you guys making a play?

15:34.309 --> 15:35.977
I'm asking you the questions.

15:35.977 --> 15:38.146
You know that's not how
newspapers work, right?

15:38.146 --> 15:40.190
It was kind of hot before
when you were talking to me

15:40.190 --> 15:41.232
about Tesla.

15:41.232 --> 15:42.650
What else do you know
about them?

15:42.650 --> 15:44.152
They're an automotive
and energy company

15:44.152 --> 15:47.739
founded in July 2003
in San Carlos, California,

15:47.739 --> 15:50.283
- but currently headquartered--
- Oh, my God, stop.

15:50.283 --> 15:52.869
Stop it.
You're so funny, Dustin.

15:52.869 --> 15:54.079
[laughs]

15:54.079 --> 15:55.872
- He called you too?
- Yup.

15:55.872 --> 15:57.415
What is going on with him?

15:57.415 --> 15:59.501
And then he was asking me
about some battery company.

15:59.501 --> 16:01.670
Me too. Sandbox.

16:01.670 --> 16:03.713
What's that about?

16:03.713 --> 16:05.173
- Well, I should go.
- Yeah, okay. Bye.

16:05.173 --> 16:07.217
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:07.217 --> 16:08.551
- Hi, I need you to look into...
- Hey, have you heard

16:08.551 --> 16:09.886
- of Sandbox?
- Called Sandbox.

16:09.886 --> 16:12.013
Wesley, Monica Chess
from the "Journal."

16:12.013 --> 16:13.807
I'm hearing rumors
about an auto company

16:13.807 --> 16:14.933
acquiring Sandbox.

16:14.933 --> 16:16.685
- Care to comment?
- You mean Tesla?

16:16.685 --> 16:18.728
Tesla? That's interesting.

16:18.728 --> 16:20.230
When you say "there's
a buzz," how much buzz?

16:20.230 --> 16:22.524
Well, I'm hearing a lot of--
oh, hold on.

16:22.524 --> 16:24.526
- Hello?
- Chucky-Cheese,

16:24.526 --> 16:26.194
checking your temperature
on Sandbox.

16:26.194 --> 16:28.530
Jesus, they're about
to explode.

16:28.530 --> 16:30.198
Tesla and Payne are
both interested?

16:30.198 --> 16:31.700
Those are just the ones
that I know of.

16:31.700 --> 16:32.951
- Lemme guess, Sandbox?
- Hold on.

16:32.951 --> 16:34.869
Hey, Monica,
I don't think anyone's talking

16:34.869 --> 16:36.371
about anything but them.

16:36.371 --> 16:38.873
Look, the company everyone
is talking about right now,

16:38.873 --> 16:40.375
Sandbox!
<i>Buy, buy, buy!</i>

16:40.375 --> 16:41.876
This thing is on fire, people.

16:41.876 --> 16:43.586
It is red-hot!
<i>[buzzing]</i>

16:43.586 --> 16:45.588
Apparently
they're the next Google,

16:45.588 --> 16:47.632
Alphabet, Facebook, Meta.

16:47.632 --> 16:48.967
I know some of those are
the same companies,

16:48.967 --> 16:50.719
but the point is,
they could've been the answer

16:50.719 --> 16:52.470
to all of our problems
and we missed it.

16:52.470 --> 16:54.889
- Uh, you missed it.
- Is it possible

16:54.889 --> 16:56.725
that we're just buyin'
into the hype?

16:56.725 --> 16:58.143
I mean, you were the one
that said they were trying

16:58.143 --> 16:59.644
- to sell us magic beans.
- Yeah.

16:59.644 --> 17:01.062
And if I remember
that story correctly,

17:01.062 --> 17:02.814
they really were magic beans.

17:02.814 --> 17:05.442
[bleep], we misread
that situation completely.

17:05.442 --> 17:06.943
You misread the situation.

17:06.943 --> 17:08.695
Okay, Wesley, you were right.

17:08.695 --> 17:10.572
Happy?
You were right. I was wrong.

17:10.572 --> 17:12.449
You were wrong.
Oh, I heard it.

17:12.449 --> 17:14.659
- [cell phone buzzes]
- Oh, it's Javier from Nissan.

17:14.659 --> 17:17.245
Everybody's thirsty
for Cyrus today.

17:17.245 --> 17:18.788
<i>Hola, Javi.</i>

17:18.788 --> 17:24.127
Chase, I'd like to apologize
for my lack of tact earlier.

17:24.127 --> 17:25.587
Oh, do you now?

17:25.587 --> 17:26.713
Your vision may have been
too bold

17:26.713 --> 17:28.256
for me to recognize right away.

17:28.256 --> 17:32.218
So how 'bout 200 million
for a 5% stake in Sandbox?

17:32.218 --> 17:34.679
200, that's--that's a lot
of money for, uh--

17:34.679 --> 17:37.390
what did you call us,
a bag of farts?

17:37.390 --> 17:39.934
I think it was actually
a battery made of farts.

17:39.934 --> 17:41.311
Once you get to know her,
that's not even

17:41.311 --> 17:43.438
all that insulting.
That's like a four out of ten.

17:43.438 --> 17:45.940
Well, an hour ago, I would've
jumped at that offer,

17:45.940 --> 17:48.860
but since then,
we have had a flood...

17:48.860 --> 17:50.362
[chuckles] Of interest.

17:50.362 --> 17:52.489
Hedge funds, VCs.

17:52.489 --> 17:55.241
Anyway, thanks for comin' back.

17:55.241 --> 17:57.535
It's been...

17:57.535 --> 17:59.162
hilarious.

17:59.162 --> 18:00.455
[sighs]

18:00.455 --> 18:05.669
If you ever hurt her,
I will kick your ass.

18:05.669 --> 18:08.463
<i>[light percussive music]</i>

18:14.511 --> 18:15.887
While the focus has been
on optimization, the issue is,

18:17.013 --> 18:19.265
